<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="379" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,747,953]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,747,773]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[418,563,747,773]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bombyliidae</taxonomicName>
is divided in two artificial groups, Homoeophthalmae and Tomophthalmae, based on postcranial features. 
<taxonomicName box="[503,596,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[503,596,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the Homoeophthalmae and the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1913" box="[1223,1349,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phthiriinae">Phthiriinae</taxonomicName>
, in this subfamily the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[387,480,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[387,480,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized from all other genera by the following characters: Metapleuron with micropubescence, first flagellomere with short and sparse hairs, costal vein ending at anal vein, male terminalia rotated 180°, basistylus without mesal lobe bearing spines, apicomesal lobe well developed, and female spermathecal reservoir curved apically (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L." box="[484,663,927,953]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref2724" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. (1990) Systematics and evolution of the genera of the subfamilies Usiinae and Phthiriinae of the world (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Entomonograph, 11, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1990">Evenhuis, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[675,1004,927,953]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="105 - 244" refId="ref2925" refString="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2001) Annotated keys to the Bombylioidea (Diptera: Bombyliidae; Mythicomyiidae) of Africa. African Invertebrates, 47, 105 - 244." type="journal article" year="2001">Greathead &amp; Evenhuis, 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
